      • getOid

        String getOid()
        Gets the object identifier of the index value described by the receiver.

        This method returns only that portion of the indexed object's OID that corresponds to the index value.

        Returns:
        object identifier substring representing the index value

      • getSyntax

        int getSyntax()
        Gets the SMI syntax indicator for the index object described by the receiver.
        Returns:
        syntax indicator

      • getEncoded

        int[] getEncoded()
        Gets the encoded form of the index value described by the receiver.

        This method returns only that portion of the indexed object's OID that corresponds to the index value.

        Returns:
        an integer array containing the OID-encoded index value

      • isImplied

        boolean isImplied()
        Gets the state of a flag indicating whether the length of the index value described by the receiver is implied (i.e. not included in the object identifier).
        Returns:
        flag state
